1
00:01:31,789 --> 00:01:34,960
[Wind Direction]

2
00:01:35,520 --> 00:01:37,950
[Episode 26]

3
00:01:40,750 --> 00:01:42,630
I was born in a fishing village.

4
00:01:42,860 --> 00:01:44,390
My home was a boat

5
00:01:44,390 --> 00:01:46,009
anchored at the shore.

6
00:01:46,670 --> 00:01:49,030
For 17 years, every step of my life

7
00:01:49,030 --> 00:01:50,590
was like weeds bending to the wind,

8
00:01:50,590 --> 00:01:52,310
wild dogs roaming the wilderness.

9
00:01:52,310 --> 00:01:52,910
I don't know

10
00:01:52,910 --> 00:01:54,229
how many days after I was born

11
00:01:54,229 --> 00:01:55,320
I was abandoned.

12
00:01:56,350 --> 00:01:57,789
Grandpa found me

13
00:01:57,789 --> 00:01:58,870
on an old boat by the sea.

14
00:01:58,870 --> 00:02:00,070
He said I was wrapped in a quilt

15
00:02:00,070 --> 00:02:01,630
with embroidered flowers.

16
00:02:01,980 --> 00:02:03,710
He believed my mother must have been afraid I'd freeze.

17
00:02:03,710 --> 00:02:05,440
She wasn't a heartless person.

18
00:02:05,790 --> 00:02:07,470
Grandpa, my older brother, and I

19
00:02:07,470 --> 00:02:08,910
struggled to survive,

20
00:02:09,080 --> 00:02:10,990
never daring to hope for more from life.

21
00:02:10,990 --> 00:02:11,990
Grandpa, I'm off to school.

22
00:02:11,990 --> 00:02:12,870
Grandpa was illiterate,

23
00:02:12,870 --> 00:02:14,270
but he firmly believed that

24
00:02:14,270 --> 00:02:16,130
education could change our fate.

25
00:02:16,620 --> 00:02:18,300
He worked more than ten hours a day,

26
00:02:18,300 --> 00:02:19,710
and every penny he earned

27
00:02:19,829 --> 00:02:22,360
went towards schooling for my brother and me.

28
00:02:22,520 --> 00:02:23,829
But even so,

29
00:02:23,870 --> 00:02:24,990
his money

30
00:02:25,070 --> 00:02:26,950
couldn't cover the cost

31
00:02:26,950 --> 00:02:28,610
of sending two kids to school.

32
00:02:29,150 --> 00:02:30,520
My brother gave up his chance

33
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:31,650
at education for me.

34
00:02:31,910 --> 00:02:32,990
He carried a quilt on his back

35
00:02:32,990 --> 00:02:34,270
and headed south.

36
00:02:34,790 --> 00:02:35,560
He said,

37
00:02:35,560 --> 00:02:37,630
"One of us has to go to school."

38
00:02:38,680 --> 00:02:39,920
Then one day,

39
00:02:39,990 --> 00:02:41,150
a group of people unlike us

40
00:02:41,150 --> 00:02:43,160
moved into the western side of the bridge.

41
00:02:43,160 --> 00:02:44,820
They were children of oilfield workers.

42
00:02:44,820 --> 00:02:46,730
Their side was always brightly lit,

43
00:02:46,730 --> 00:02:48,930
filled with laughter and joy.

44
00:02:49,910 --> 00:02:50,710
A single bridge

45
00:02:50,710 --> 00:02:52,110
separated two fates.

46
00:02:52,750 --> 00:02:54,020
I often sat on the bridge,

47
00:02:54,020 --> 00:02:56,360
looking toward the other side of the bridge.

48
00:02:56,360 --> 00:02:57,510
I studied harder, hoping to escape

49
00:02:57,510 --> 00:02:59,570
the misery of this side of the bridge.

50
00:03:01,110 --> 00:03:02,950
But poverty still strangled

51
00:03:02,950 --> 00:03:04,350
this one and only chance.

52
00:03:05,310 --> 00:03:06,350
They could choose

53
00:03:06,350 --> 00:03:07,470
a better life,

54
00:03:07,590 --> 00:03:08,990
but generation after generation,

55
00:03:08,990 --> 00:03:10,430
they followed the oil pumps,

56
00:03:10,430 --> 00:03:12,760
dedicating their youth and entire lives.

57
00:03:13,350 --> 00:03:14,920
I got the chance to go to school,

58
00:03:14,920 --> 00:03:17,310
and I found a group of wonderful friends.

59
00:03:17,750 --> 00:03:19,310
We were all nourished

60
00:03:19,310 --> 00:03:20,040
by this land.

61
00:03:20,230 --> 00:03:20,990
In the end,

62
00:03:21,030 --> 00:03:22,270
we are all the same.

63
00:03:22,790 --> 00:03:25,180
[Early Summer]

64
00:03:25,590 --> 00:03:30,910
[Linqi Oilfield Staff Hospital]

65
00:03:40,650 --> 00:03:41,460
Min.

66
00:03:42,390 --> 00:03:44,430
Uncle Cheng, where is he?

67
00:03:44,690 --> 00:03:45,670
He's in surgery.

68
00:03:46,740 --> 00:03:47,940
Is it serious?

69
00:03:48,710 --> 00:03:49,390
Min.

70
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:51,800
Prepare yourself mentally.

71
00:03:52,579 --> 00:03:54,440
Yang is seriously hurt this time.

72
00:03:55,670 --> 00:03:57,630
Where... where is he hurt?

73
00:03:59,620 --> 00:04:00,590
Is his blood pressure stable?

74
00:04:00,590 --> 00:04:01,710
It's stable now.

75
00:04:01,930 --> 00:04:03,480
Are you a family member of Yang Songbai?

76
00:04:03,480 --> 00:04:04,590
I'm his daughter.

77
00:04:04,610 --> 00:04:05,790
Please take a look at the surgery consent form.

78
00:04:05,790 --> 00:04:06,510
If everything looks fine,

79
00:04:06,510 --> 00:04:07,490
sign at the bottom.

80
00:04:07,490 --> 00:04:08,100
Nurse.

81
00:04:08,870 --> 00:04:09,470
What's

82
00:04:09,870 --> 00:04:10,910
the situation inside right now?

83
00:04:10,910 --> 00:04:11,710
Where is he hurt?

84
00:04:11,710 --> 00:04:12,910
Is he in danger?

85
00:04:12,910 --> 00:04:14,150
We don't know yet.

86
00:04:14,150 --> 00:04:15,110
He's still unconscious.

87
00:04:15,110 --> 00:04:16,290
We're doing everything we can.

88
00:04:16,290 --> 00:04:17,350
Come, sign here first.

89
00:04:17,350 --> 00:04:18,950
He's in critical condition?

90
00:04:23,510 --> 00:04:24,830
Will everything be fine

91
00:04:24,830 --> 00:04:25,630
once the surgery is done?

92
00:04:25,630 --> 00:04:27,270
We'll do our best.

93
00:04:27,570 --> 00:04:28,360
Your best...

94
00:04:31,230 --> 00:04:32,140
Uncle Cheng.

95
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:33,430
Yang.

96
00:04:33,430 --> 00:04:34,190
-He...
-Min, Min, Min.

97
00:04:34,190 --> 00:04:35,230
Dr. Chen is the best doctor

98
00:04:35,230 --> 00:04:36,230
we have here.

99
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:38,080
We can trust him.

100
00:04:42,550 --> 00:04:46,380
[In Operation]

101
00:05:10,150 --> 00:05:10,950
Xiao Fang.

102
00:05:13,330 --> 00:05:15,330
Director Xiao went to the hospital.

103
00:05:15,870 --> 00:05:16,750
What happened to her?

104
00:05:16,750 --> 00:05:17,270
She got injured

105
00:05:17,270 --> 00:05:18,430
while helping with the flood rescue efforts

106
00:05:18,430 --> 00:05:19,070
at school.

107
00:05:27,710 --> 00:05:28,710
Zi is asleep?

108
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:32,200
She didn't sleep well last night because of the thunderstorm.

109
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:33,600
Have some noodles first.

110
00:05:44,670 --> 00:05:45,430
Do you think

111
00:05:46,590 --> 00:05:48,150
Uncle Yang will be fine?

112
00:05:49,350 --> 00:05:50,350
He should be fine.

113
00:05:50,710 --> 00:05:51,640
My dad's at the hospital.

114
00:05:51,640 --> 00:05:52,590
Leave it to them.

115
00:06:01,950 --> 00:06:02,540
Hello.

116
00:06:03,310 --> 00:06:04,110
Yaya.

117
00:06:04,710 --> 00:06:05,380
Aunt Yue.

118
00:06:08,590 --> 00:06:10,060
I just called home.

119
00:06:10,060 --> 00:06:11,560
Min wasn't there.

120
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:13,200
Is she at your place?

121
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:14,920
Aunt Yue, something happened.

122
00:06:14,920 --> 00:06:16,110
Wait, don't hang up.

123
00:06:16,110 --> 00:06:17,440
I'll let my mom explain.

124
00:06:18,990 --> 00:06:20,190
Something happened?

125
00:06:20,390 --> 00:06:22,060
Mom. Mom.

126
00:06:22,510 --> 00:06:23,550
Aunt Yue called.

127
00:06:23,550 --> 00:06:24,810
You should talk to her.

128
00:06:31,590 --> 00:06:32,360
Hello?

129
00:06:33,070 --> 00:06:33,950
Yue.

130
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:35,990
Yaya just told me something happened.

131
00:06:35,990 --> 00:06:37,060
What's going on?

132
00:06:37,470 --> 00:06:39,070
Did something happen to Min?

133
00:06:39,950 --> 00:06:41,180
No,

134
00:06:41,270 --> 00:06:42,710
no,

135
00:06:43,159 --> 00:06:44,330
nothing happened.

136
00:06:44,640 --> 00:06:46,010
We're all fine here,

137
00:06:46,110 --> 00:06:46,830
Don't worry.

138
00:06:46,830 --> 00:06:47,670
How's everything

139
00:06:47,670 --> 00:06:48,909
in Beijing?

140
00:06:49,330 --> 00:06:50,060
Yu.

141
00:06:50,190 --> 00:06:52,030
I called home,

142
00:06:52,030 --> 00:06:52,750
but no one picked up.

143
00:06:52,750 --> 00:06:53,750
I can't find Min.

144
00:06:53,750 --> 00:06:55,350
Did something happen to her?

145
00:06:55,550 --> 00:06:57,030
Min's doing great.

146
00:06:57,030 --> 00:06:57,909
We're all taking good care of her.

147
00:06:57,909 --> 00:06:58,850
Don't worry.

148
00:06:58,990 --> 00:07:00,080
She's out with Miaomiao

149
00:07:00,080 --> 00:07:01,210
right now, playing.

150
00:07:01,430 --> 00:07:02,990
But I saw the weather forecast—

151
00:07:02,990 --> 00:07:04,650
it's pouring down where you are.

152
00:07:04,650 --> 00:07:06,050
Where did they go to play?

153
00:07:06,500 --> 00:07:07,490
Yeah, it's raining,

154
00:07:07,490 --> 00:07:08,750
but you know how kids are.

155
00:07:08,750 --> 00:07:10,350
Even rain can't stop them.

156
00:07:10,470 --> 00:07:11,310
Once she's back,

157
00:07:11,310 --> 00:07:12,150
I'll have her give you a call,

158
00:07:12,150 --> 00:07:13,070
so don't worry.

159
00:07:13,430 --> 00:07:15,240
Are you hiding something from me?

160
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:16,520
No.

161
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:20,300
Did something happen to Yang?

162
00:07:21,230 --> 00:07:22,850
She's asking if something happened to Yang.

163
00:07:22,850 --> 00:07:24,090
Let me.

164
00:07:24,900 --> 00:07:25,620
Hello?

165
00:07:25,640 --> 00:07:26,910
Yue, it's me.

166
00:07:27,270 --> 00:07:28,710
What could possibly happen to Yang?

167
00:07:28,710 --> 00:07:30,440
He's still at the No. 3 Factory.

168
00:07:30,670 --> 00:07:31,550
Besides,

169
00:07:31,810 --> 00:07:33,190
aren't you two divorced?

170
00:07:33,190 --> 00:07:34,670
Why are you still worried about him?

171
00:07:34,670 --> 00:07:35,750
As for Min,

172
00:07:35,810 --> 00:07:37,150
we'll talk to her when she gets back.

173
00:07:37,150 --> 00:07:37,880
Don't worry.

174
00:07:37,990 --> 00:07:39,750
This is a long-distance call. It's expensive.

175
00:07:39,750 --> 00:07:40,430
I've got to go out

176
00:07:40,430 --> 00:07:41,190
with Daiyu soon,

177
00:07:41,190 --> 00:07:42,030
so let's hang up now, okay?

178
00:07:42,030 --> 00:07:43,030
Bye.

179
00:07:49,060 --> 00:07:50,190
Take off your pants.

180
00:07:50,430 --> 00:07:51,030
Alright.

181
00:07:52,520 --> 00:07:53,240
Xiao Fang!

182
00:07:54,120 --> 00:07:54,760
Xiao Fang!

183
00:07:55,159 --> 00:07:56,460
Where exactly are you hurt?

184
00:07:56,460 --> 00:07:57,530
How did this happen?

185
00:07:57,530 --> 00:07:58,350
Weren't you helping with the rescue efforts?

186
00:07:58,350 --> 00:07:59,270
How did you end up in the hospital?

187
00:07:59,270 --> 00:07:59,510
No.

188
00:07:59,510 --> 00:08:00,750
Where did you get hurt?

189
00:08:00,750 --> 00:08:01,310
Sir.

190
00:08:01,310 --> 00:08:02,630
Sir, calm down.

191
00:08:02,660 --> 00:08:03,610
Her injuries aren't serious.

192
00:08:03,610 --> 00:08:04,530
Not serious?

193
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:05,350
I can barely recognize you!

194
00:08:05,350 --> 00:08:06,910
Did you use your face to do the rescue?

195
00:08:06,910 --> 00:08:08,110
Keep your voice down.

196
00:08:08,410 --> 00:08:09,470
I fell into a ditch.

197
00:08:09,660 --> 00:08:10,260
What?

198
00:08:10,350 --> 00:08:11,460
Fell into a ditch?

199
00:08:12,180 --> 00:08:13,310
How could you be so careless?

200
00:08:13,310 --> 00:08:14,720
Sir, can you step out for a moment?

201
00:08:14,720 --> 00:08:15,640
She has a wound.

202
00:08:15,670 --> 00:08:17,070
She needs a tetanus shot.

203
00:08:19,580 --> 00:08:20,980
A shot in the butt, right?

204
00:08:21,230 --> 00:08:22,890
Alright, go ahead and give it.

205
00:08:22,910 --> 00:08:24,130
I'll just wait by the door.

206
00:08:24,130 --> 00:08:25,060
Don't be scared.

207
00:08:25,740 --> 00:08:26,340
Be good.

208
00:08:27,310 --> 00:08:29,560
[Treatment Room]

209
00:08:30,570 --> 00:08:31,970
Take it easy, slowly now.

210
00:08:33,570 --> 00:08:34,809
Why on a rainy day like this,

211
00:08:34,809 --> 00:08:36,090
instead of staying safe in your dorm,

212
00:08:36,090 --> 00:08:37,179
did you run out?

213
00:08:37,770 --> 00:08:38,940
The school was flooded.

214
00:08:38,940 --> 00:08:40,860
I had to go help with the rescue efforts.

215
00:08:40,860 --> 00:08:41,970
You're not even taller than the sandbags.

216
00:08:41,970 --> 00:08:42,860
Who are you going to save?

217
00:08:42,860 --> 00:08:44,540
You're just causing more trouble.

218
00:08:44,540 --> 00:08:45,460
I'm telling you,

219
00:08:45,460 --> 00:08:47,010
it's lucky it was just a nail in there.

220
00:08:47,010 --> 00:08:47,660
If it had been a knife,

221
00:08:47,660 --> 00:08:49,190
you could've lost your leg.

222
00:08:49,490 --> 00:08:51,210
It sounds like you'd be happy if I died!

223
00:08:51,210 --> 00:08:52,450
What are you saying?

224
00:08:52,550 --> 00:08:53,820
When I found out you were in the hospital,

225
00:08:53,820 --> 00:08:54,960
my legs nearly gave out.

226
00:08:54,960 --> 00:08:55,500
My heart rate

227
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:56,380
shot up to 200!

228
00:08:56,380 --> 00:08:57,460
200?

229
00:08:57,490 --> 00:08:58,770
Then you should be the one in the hospital.

230
00:08:58,770 --> 00:08:59,540
Don't believe me?

231
00:08:59,540 --> 00:08:59,860
Feel it.

232
00:08:59,860 --> 00:09:01,060
It's still pounding.

233
00:09:12,060 --> 00:09:14,020
I'm sorry to make you worry?

234
00:09:15,540 --> 00:09:18,140
Just don't make me worry like that again, okay?

235
00:09:18,260 --> 00:09:18,850
Let's go.

236
00:09:20,420 --> 00:09:22,470
[In Operation]

237
00:09:23,660 --> 00:09:24,260
It's done.

238
00:09:26,660 --> 00:09:27,330
Dr. Wang,

239
00:09:27,900 --> 00:09:28,900
how's Yang doing?

240
00:09:29,010 --> 00:09:30,060
He hasn't woken up yet,

241
00:09:30,060 --> 00:09:30,540
but there's

242
00:09:30,540 --> 00:09:32,260
no immediate danger to his life.

243
00:09:32,260 --> 00:09:33,580
Where's he hurt?

244
00:09:33,780 --> 00:09:34,490
His spine.

245
00:09:35,660 --> 00:09:36,570
Doctor,

246
00:09:36,570 --> 00:09:37,940
when will he wake up?

247
00:09:40,740 --> 00:09:41,410
Coming.

248
00:09:46,150 --> 00:09:47,440
The rain finally stopped.

249
00:09:47,440 --> 00:09:48,170
Are you okay?

250
00:09:48,180 --> 00:09:49,040
I'm exhausted.

251
00:09:51,090 --> 00:09:51,980
Dahai.

252
00:09:52,020 --> 00:09:53,500
You really scared me!

253
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:54,620
I'm so worried!

254
00:09:54,620 --> 00:09:56,420
You didn't even call me!

255
00:09:56,730 --> 00:09:57,540
I'm fine.

256
00:09:57,540 --> 00:09:58,260
What if

257
00:09:58,260 --> 00:09:59,740
something happened to you

258
00:09:59,740 --> 00:10:01,060
like it did to Yang?

259
00:10:01,620 --> 00:10:03,940
What would I do?

260
00:10:04,530 --> 00:10:05,340
Yang?

261
00:10:05,740 --> 00:10:07,000
What happened to Yang?

262
00:10:08,060 --> 00:10:09,140
What do you mean?

263
00:10:09,740 --> 00:10:10,950
If he doesn't wake up,

264
00:10:11,630 --> 00:10:14,790
Yang might become a vegetable?

265
00:10:24,180 --> 00:10:24,900
Miaomiao.

266
00:10:25,060 --> 00:10:27,190
You know, I used to really dislike him.

267
00:10:27,650 --> 00:10:29,090
He was always arguing with my mom,

268
00:10:29,090 --> 00:10:30,060
and I wanted them

269
00:10:30,060 --> 00:10:32,060
to get divorced as soon as possible.

270
00:10:32,780 --> 00:10:35,060
Now they're divorced,

271
00:10:35,780 --> 00:10:36,850
but I never thought

272
00:10:36,850 --> 00:10:38,570
he'd end up like this.

273
00:10:38,620 --> 00:10:40,500
I just want him to be okay.

274
00:10:41,860 --> 00:10:42,660
The other day,

275
00:10:42,950 --> 00:10:44,790
I even went to see him

276
00:10:45,490 --> 00:10:46,900
on the platform at sea.

277
00:10:46,900 --> 00:10:47,980
He looked so commanding,

278
00:10:47,980 --> 00:10:48,980
leading his team.

279
00:10:49,340 --> 00:10:50,460
I'd never seen him like that before,

280
00:10:50,460 --> 00:10:51,700
completely different

281
00:10:51,700 --> 00:10:53,260
from how he is at home.

282
00:10:53,650 --> 00:10:56,410
How did things turn out like this?

283
00:10:56,720 --> 00:10:57,760
He even said that,

284
00:10:57,980 --> 00:10:59,020
in the future,

285
00:11:00,210 --> 00:11:01,680
we'd still be a family.

286
00:11:02,780 --> 00:11:03,420
But

287
00:11:05,020 --> 00:11:06,950
when I was in the hospital that day,

288
00:11:07,620 --> 00:11:10,380
I felt so awful inside.

289
00:11:11,630 --> 00:11:13,830
It was my signature on his surgery form,

290
00:11:14,380 --> 00:11:15,090
but

291
00:11:16,860 --> 00:11:19,260
I'm not even his family anymore.

292
00:11:19,510 --> 00:11:20,700
They're divorced.

293
00:11:21,580 --> 00:11:23,620
I'm not even his daughter legally.

294
00:11:25,540 --> 00:11:26,940
And yet, he had no one else

295
00:11:26,940 --> 00:11:30,340
to sign for him for the surgery.

296
00:11:33,810 --> 00:11:36,620
How did it end up like this?

297
00:11:44,380 --> 00:11:47,260
It was an emergency.

298
00:11:47,260 --> 00:11:48,260
Your brother lives far away

